Package: libplcode-dev
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Description: Two-way radio signaling codec library (CTCSS/DCS/DTMF/CW ID)
 libplcode is a portable C99 library for encoding and decoding two-way radio
 signaling tones and codes in signed 16-bit linear PCM audio. It supports
 CTCSS (PL) tones, DCS (DPL) codes, DTMF tones, CW ID (Morse code),
 MCW (Modulated CW), FSK CW, Two-Tone Sequential Paging, Five-Tone Selective
 Call (ZVEI/CCIR/EIA), MDC-1200 signaling, tone burst access, and courtesy
 tones.
 .
 The library uses fixed-point DSP throughout with zero external dependencies
 beyond libc and libm. All codecs follow a create/process/destroy lifecycle
 with opaque context structs and allocation-free streaming.
 .
 This package provides the static library and development header.
